

INSTALLATION:
	MUST HAVE SDL LIBRARIES INSTALLED
		-In order to run TackleTag all SDL libraries must be installed
	RUN MAKE FILE
		- In order to compile the program simply run the makefile by using the `make` 
	          command in the project repository.
		
ENVIRONMENTS:
	TackleTag was built in the Linux Red Hat Environment, it should intheory be able to run on 	any machine which has the SDL libraries installed, but all environments could not be tested. 	Performance on other platforms cannot be guaranteed.
	
INSTRUCTIONS:
	-Run main
	-Press ‘space’ to begin. Avoid the USC Player by moving using the arrow keys and rack up 	 points.
	-Collect coins for extra points
	-Hit ‘space’ to play again
		
FUTURE UPDATES?:
	-Store high scores locally
	-Enhanced graphics/sound
	-iPhone/Android version
